<DESCRIPT>  ENTERTAINMENT  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  You're sick of Scrabble. Backgammon gives you the blahs. Board games are mere
trivial pursuits.;   But there are a whole new shelf of role-playing games and
quizzes out there. "Getting to Know You . . . Better" ($25) focuses on
developing the kind of chit-chat couples used to share on first dates. "How to
Host a Romantic Evening" ($25) uses recipes and suggestions to let "players
take a journey of the mind!" Yeah, right. And straight into the boudoir.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  JUST ROLE THE DICE  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  What's Hot  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Meanwhile "You Just Became a Millionaire" ($25) focuses on more concrete
things as players answer questions about their newfound fictional wealth.
"It's one thing to be rich, but to really feel rich I will . . . ". Um, buy a
"Getting to Know Your Accountant . . . Better" game?; GETTING OUT; TODAY:
"John Cage: Prints from Crown Point Press and Other Works," plus recent work
by David Hannah open today at the Stanford Art Gallery, near Hoover Tower on
the Stanford University Campus. A reception will be held today, 5 p.m.-7 p.m.
(415) 723-2842.  </TEXT>
